Section 1:
1 L.D. 898
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 LABOR
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 387, L.D. 898, “An Act to Support Rural
10 Workforce Recruitment by Allowing Pay Differentials Based on Work Site Location and
11 Employee Experience and Credentials Under the Maine Equal Pay Law”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'Resolve, to Support Rural Health Care Workforce Recruitment'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
15 'Emergency preamble. Whereas, acts and resolves of the Legislature do not
16 become effective until 90 days after adjournment unless enacted as emergencies; and
17 Whereas, the State is experiencing a serious shortage of health care providers,
18 particularly in rural communities; and
19 Whereas, the changes to the Department of Labor's rules relating to equal pay
20 provided for in this legislation are designed to alleviate that health care provider shortage;
21 and
22 Whereas, in the judgment of the Legislature, these facts create an emergency within
23 the meaning of the Constitution of Maine and require the following legislation as
24 immediately necessary for the preservation of the public peace, health and safety; now,
25 therefore, be it
26 Sec. 1. Department of Labor; rulemaking. Resolved: That the Department of
27 Labor shall initiate rulemaking to amend its Bureau of Labor Standards rule Chapter 12:
28 Rules Relating to Equal Pay, as follows:
29 1. The rule must be amended in Section I(G) to clarify, for the purposes of the
30 definition of "establishment," that different entities or facilities operated by a hospital or
31 health care entity at different physical locations are not considered a single establishment;
32 and
Page 1 - 132LR1637(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 387, L.D. 898
1 2. The rule must be amended in Section I(K) to clarify, for the purposes of the
2 definition of "seniority system," that preference under a seniority system must be given to
3 workers based on years of service or based on pertinent experience or credentials.
4 The rule changes directed under this section must be finally adopted by the department
5 no later than October 1, 2025. Rules adopted pursuant to this section are routine technical
6 rules as defined in the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 5, chapter 375, subchapter 2-A.
7 Emergency clause. In view of the emergency cited in the preamble, this legislation
8 takes effect when approved.'
9 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
10 number to read consecutively.
11 SUMMARY
1122 This amendment replaces the bill with a resolve and directs the Department of Labor
1133 to amend its Bureau of Labor Standards rule Chapter 12: Rules Relating to Equal Pay to
1144 make clarifications under that rule to the definitions of "establishment" and "seniority
1155 system." Those rule changes must be accomplished through routine technical rulemaking
1166 and must be finally adopted by the department no later than October 1, 2025.
1177 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
1188 (See attached)
Page 2 - 132LR1637(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
